-- EDS profit net up as contract signings rise 27 percent
-- 
-- Mon Jul 28, 2008 5:16pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/28/us-eds-results-idUSWNAB303620080728

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - Electronic Data Systems Corp EDS.N, the second-largest technology outsourcing company, on Monday posted higher-than-expected quarterly earnings and said contract signings rose 27 percent from the year ago. 

 Net income rose to $160 million, or 31 cents per share, from $138 million, or 26 cents per share a year earlier, the Plano, Texas-based company said. EDS also said contract signings rose to $5.4 billion from $4.3 billion a year earlier and were particularly strong in the government and financial services sectors Adjusted earnings of 33 cents a share topped analysts' average estimate of 26 cents a share, according to Reuters Estimates. Revenue rose to $5.62 billion from $5.45 billion. Analysts had expected revenue of $5.7 billion, on average. Shares ticked up in light after-hours trading to $24.89 from a Nasdaq close of $24.79. Hewlett-Packard Co ( HPQ.N ) has won regulatory approval to buy Plano, Texas-based EDS for $13.2 billion, including options and restricted stock, in a deal aimed at helping HP compete better against IBM. (Reporting by Alex Dobuzinskis: Editing by Leslie Gevirtz and Carol Bishopric)